genresAdvancedInfo.name: traditional funk
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Traditional funk is a genre of music that emerged in the 1960s and 1970s. It is characterized by its heavy emphasis on rhythm and groove, often featuring intricate bass lines, syncopated drums, and brass instruments. Traditional funk draws heavily from African American musical traditions, including jazz, soul, and R&B, and has had a significant influence on popular music ever since.
